orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_2f14816e14f375768c7118335f1ec3a5" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_89404785d2e77a7499badeef082586ae" parent="aspace_2f14816e14f375768c7118335f1ec3a5" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_9269d46a670586c5bda39870cfec0a78" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_20d28fc62069822f4a329e8284a98ca3" parent="aspace_9269d46a670586c5bda39870cfec0a78" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_d9c29e2b9f5490497c8094221e1e1706" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_b61b9aced2da022ee98878ec420badae" parent="aspace_d9c29e2b9f5490497c8094221e1e1706" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-